65.4	Natural_building	Natural building	One of the oldest building methods, adobe is simply clay and sand mixed with water. Sometimes chopped straw or other fibers are added for strength. The mixture is then allowed to dry in the desired shape. Usually adobe is shaped into bricks that can be stacked to form walls.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/98/Timber_frame_detail.jpg/400px-Timber_frame_detail.jpg
